name: Our Planet
synopsis: Documentary series focusing on the breadth of the diversity of habitats around the world, from the remote Arctic wilderness and mysterious deep oceans to the vast landscapes of Africa and diverse jungles of South America.

name: The Last Dance
synopsis: Charting the rise of the 1990s Chicago Bulls, led by Michael Jordan, one of the most notable dynasties in sports history.

name: When They See Us
synopsis: Five teens from Harlem become trapped in a nightmare when they're falsely accused of a brutal attack in Central Park. Based on the true story.

name: Black Mirror
synopsis: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.

name: Narcos
synopsis: A chronicled look at the criminal exploits of Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar, as well as the many other drug kingpins who plagued the country through the years.

name: Dark
synopsis: A family saga with a supernatural twist, set in a German town where the disappearance of two young children exposes the relationships among four families.

name: Stranger Things
synopsis: When a young boy disappears, his mother, a police chief and his friends must confront terrifying supernatural forces in order to get him back.

name: House of Cards
synopsis: A Congressman works with his equally conniving wife to exact revenge on the people who betrayed him.

name: Arrested Development
synopsis: Level-headed son Michael Bluth takes over family affairs after his father is imprisoned. But the rest of his spoiled, dysfunctional family are making his job unbearable.

name: The Crown
synopsis: Follows the political rivalries and romance of Queen Elizabeth II's reign and the events that shaped the second half of the twentieth century.

name: BoJack Horseman
synopsis: BoJack Horseman was the star of the hit television show "Horsin' Around" in the '80s and '90s, but now he's washed up, living in Hollywood, complaining about everything, and wearing colorful sweaters.

name: Anne
synopsis: The adventures of a young orphan girl living in the early 19th century. Follow Anne as she learns to navigate her new life on Prince Edward Island, in this new take on L.M. Montgomery's classic novels.

name: Formula 1: Drive to Survive
synopsis: Docuseries following the FIA Formula One World Championship across multiple seasons.

name: Daredevil
synopsis: A blind lawyer by day, vigilante by night. Matt Murdock fights the crime of New York as Daredevil.

name: The Queen's Gambit
synopsis: Orphaned at the tender age of nine, prodigious introvert Beth Harmon discovers and masters the game of chess in 1960s USA. But child stardom comes at a price.

name: Mindhunter
synopsis: Set in the late 1970s, two FBI agents are tasked with interviewing serial killers to solve open cases.

name: The Haunting of Hill House
synopsis: Flashing between past and present, a fractured family confronts haunting memories of their old home and the terrifying events that drove them from it.

name: Making a Murderer
synopsis: Filmed over a 10-year period, Steven Avery, a DNA exoneree who, while in the midst of exposing corruption in local law enforcement, finds himself the prime suspect in a grisly new crime.

name: Sacred Games
synopsis: A link in their pasts leads an honest cop to a fugitive gang boss, whose cryptic warning spurs the officer on a quest to save Mumbai from cataclysm.

name: Hilda
synopsis: A fearless blue-haired girl named Hilda leaves the forest to go to town and find new friends, great adventures, magic and mysterious creatures who might be dangerous.

name: The Punisher
synopsis: After his revenge on those who murdered his family, aimless Marine veteran Frank Castle finds a new meaning in life as a vigilante known as "The Punisher".

name: Love, Death & Robots
synopsis: A collection of animated short stories that span various genres including science fiction, fantasy, horror and comedy.

name: Trailer Park Boys
synopsis: Three petty felons have a documentary made about their life in a trailer park.

name: Trollhunters
synopsis: An ordinary boy finds a magic amulet that chooses him to be a Trollhunter, a guardian that defends the world of humans and the secret world of trolls.

name: Chef's Table
synopsis: Chef's Table goes inside the lives and kitchens of six of the world's most renowned international chefs. Each episode focuses on a single chef and their unique look at their lives, talents and passion from their piece of culinary heaven.

name: Ozark
synopsis: A financial advisor drags his family from Chicago to the Missouri Ozarks, where he must launder money to appease a drug boss.

name: The Last Kingdom
synopsis: As Alfred the Great defends his kingdom from Norse invaders, Uhtred--born a Saxon but raised by Vikings--seeks to claim his ancestral birthright.

name: After Life
synopsis: After Tony's wife dies, his nice-guy persona is altered into an impulsive, devil-may-care attitude that takes his old world by storm.

name: Unbelievable
synopsis: A teenager is charged with lying about having been raped, but two detectives follow the path to the truth.

name: Narcos: México
synopsis: The rise of the Guadalajara Cartel as an American DEA agent learns the danger of targeting narcos in Mexico.

name: O Mecanismo
synopsis: Dramatic fiction series loosely inspired by an investigation of corruption in Brazil's private and state oil companies and construction companies.

name: Kingdom
synopsis: While strange rumors about their ill King grip a kingdom, the crown prince becomes their only hope against a mysterious plague overtaking the land.

name: The Dark Crystal: Age of Resistance
synopsis: Return to the world of Thra, where three Gelfling discover the horrifying secret behind the Skeksis' power, and set out to ignite the fires of rebellion and save their world.

name: The Dragon Prince
synopsis: Two human princes forge an unlikely bond with the elfin assassin sent to kill them, embarking on an epic quest to bring peace to their warring lands.

name: Julie and the Phantoms
synopsis: Julie is a teenage girl who finds her passion for music and life with the help of a high -concept band of teen boys (The Phantoms) who have been dead for 25 years. Julie, in turn, helps them become the band they were never able to be.

name: Last Chance U
synopsis: Intense look inside the world of junior college football, chronicling the stories of players and coaches in the classroom and on the field.

name: La casa de papel
synopsis: An unusual group of robbers attempt to carry out the most perfect robbery in Spanish history - stealing 2.4 billion euros from the Royal Mint of Spain.

name: Sex Education
synopsis: A teenage boy with a sex therapist mother teams up with a high school classmate to set up an underground sex therapy clinic at school.

name: Sense8
synopsis: A group of people around the world are suddenly linked mentally, and must find a way to survive being hunted by those who see them as a threat to the world's order.

name: Master of None
synopsis: The personal and professional life of Dev, a 30-year-old actor in New York.

name: Atypical
synopsis: Sam, an 18-year-old on the autism spectrum, decides it's time to find a girlfriend, which sets Sam's mom on her own life-changing path as her son seeks more independence.

name: Godless
synopsis: In the 1880s American West, murderous outlaw gang leader Frank Griffin hunts for ex-protege Roy Goode. Frank's chase leads him to La Belle, New Mexico--a town inhabited, after a mining disaster, almost entirely by women.

name: Grace and Frankie
synopsis: Finding out that their husbands are not just work partners, but have also been romantically involved for the last twenty years, two women with an already strained relationship try to cope with the circumstances together.

name: Longmire
synopsis: Walt Longmire is the dedicated and unflappable sheriff of Absaroka County, Wyoming. Widowed only a year, he is a man in psychic repair but buries his pain behind his brave face, unassuming grin and dry wit.

name: The Get Down
synopsis: A ragtag group of teenagers run wild in the streets of the Bronx in the late 1970s.

name: The Midnight Gospel
synopsis: Clancy, a spacecaster with a malfunctioning multiverse simulator, leaves the comfort of his home to interview beings living in dying worlds.

name: Patriot Act with Hasan Minhaj
synopsis: In this weekly show, the former Daily Show correspondent Hasan Minhaj brings his unique comedic voice and storytelling skill to explore the larger grim trends shaping our fragmented world.

name: The Witcher
synopsis: Geralt of Rivia, a solitary monster hunter, struggles to find his place in a world where people often prove more wicked than beasts.

name: The Killing
synopsis: A police investigation, the saga of a grieving family, and a Seattle mayoral campaign all interlock after the body of 17-year-old Rosie Larsen is found in the trunk of a submerged car.

name: Castlevania
synopsis: A vampire hunter fights to save a besieged city from an army of otherworldly creatures controlled by Dracula.

name: American Vandal
synopsis: A true-crime satire that explores the aftermath of a costly high school prank that left twenty-seven faculty cars vandalized with phallic images.

name: Wild Wild Country
synopsis: When Osho, the world's most controversial guru, builds an Utopian city deep in the Oregon country, conflict with the locals escalates into a national scandal.

name: The Kominsky Method
synopsis: An aging actor, who long ago enjoyed a brush with fame, makes his living as an acting coach.

name: One Day at a Time
synopsis: Follows three generations of the same Cuban-American family living in the same house: a newly divorced former military mother, her teenage daughter and tween son, and her old-school mother.

name: The Trials of Gabriel Fernandez
synopsis: Filmmaker Brian Knappenberger investigates the tragic death of an 8-year-old California boy who endured horrific abuse by his mother and her boyfriend, along with the fractured and complex systems that failed to protect him.

name: Lucifer
synopsis: Lucifer Morningstar has decided he's had enough of being the dutiful servant in Hell and decides to spend some time on Earth to better understand humanity. He settles in Los Angeles - the City of Angels.

name: The End of the F***ing World
synopsis: James is 17 and is pretty sure he is a psychopath. Alyssa, also 17, is the cool and moody new girl at school. The pair make a connection and she persuades him to embark on a road trip in search of her real father.

name: Travelers
synopsis: Hundreds of years from now, surviving humans discover how to send consciousness back through time, into people of the 21st century, while attempting to change the path of humanity.

name: The Keepers
synopsis: A seven-part docuseries about the unsolved murder of a nun and the horrific secrets and pain that linger nearly five decades after her death.

name: Lovesick
synopsis: After finding out he has an STD, Dylan must get back in touch with every girl he has ever had sex with to let them know the bad news.

name: Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee
synopsis: Jerry Seinfeld is joined by friends for a cup of coffee and a drive in a classic car, sharing stories all along the way.

name: Dota: Dragon's Blood
synopsis: After encounters with a dragon and a princess on her own mission, a Dragon Knight becomes embroiled in events larger than he could have ever imagined.

name: Dirty Money
synopsis: A Netflix Original Series documenting various stories about exposing the greed, corruption, and crime spreading through the global economy.

name: Voltron: Legendary Defender
synopsis: Five teenagers become the last line of defense for the galaxy in an intergalactic battle against the evil alien force led by King Zarkon.

name: Orange Is the New Black
synopsis: Convicted of a decade old crime of transporting drug money to an ex-girlfriend, normally law-abiding Piper Chapman is sentenced to a year and a half behind bars to face the reality of how life-changing prison can really be.

name: The Umbrella Academy
synopsis: A family of former child heroes, now grown apart, must reunite to continue to protect the world.

name: Altered Carbon
synopsis: Set in a future where consciousness is digitized and stored, a prisoner returns to life in a new body and must solve a mind-bending murder to win his freedom.

name: Marco Polo
synopsis: In a world replete with greed, betrayal, sexual intrigue and rivalry, "Marco Polo" is based on the famed explorer's adventures in Kublai Khan's court in 13th century Mongolia.

name: Unorthodox
synopsis: Story of a young ultra-Orthodox Jewish woman who flees her arranged marriage and religious community to start a new life abroad.

name: Dead to Me
synopsis: A series about a powerful friendship that blossoms between a tightly wound widow and a free spirit with a shocking secret.

name: Big Mouth
synopsis: Teenage friends find their lives upended by the wonders and horrors of puberty.

name: GLOW
synopsis: A look at the personal and professional lives of a group of women who perform for a wrestling organization in Los Angeles during the 1980s.

name: Don't F**k with Cats: Hunting an Internet Killer
synopsis: A group of online justice seekers track down a guy who posted a video of himself killing kittens.

name: F Is for Family
synopsis: Follow the Murphy family back to the 1970s, when kids roamed wild, beer flowed freely and nothing came between a man and his TV.

name: Lilyhammer
synopsis: A New York mobster goes into hiding in rural Lillehammer in Norway after testifying against his former associates.

name: Rise of Empires: Ottoman
synopsis: Ottoman Sultan Mehmed II wages an epic campaign to take the Byzantine capital of Constantinople and shapes the course of history for centuries.

name: On My Block
synopsis: A coming-of-age story about four bright, street-savvy friends navigating their way through high school in the gritty South Central Los Angeles, trying to get their friend out of a gang, and having friendship turn into something more.

name: Dragons: Riders of Berk
synopsis: The further adventures of Hiccup and his friends on the Island of Berk.

name: Jessica Jones
synopsis: Following the tragic end of her brief superhero career, Jessica Jones tries to rebuild her life as a private investigator, dealing with cases involving people with remarkable abilities in New York City.

name: The OA
synopsis: Having gone missing seven years ago, the previously blind Prairie returns home, now in her twenties with her sight restored. While many believe she is a miracle, others worry that she could be dangerous.

name: Russian Doll
synopsis: A cynical young woman in New York City keeps dying and returning to the party that's being thrown in her honor on that same evening. She tries to find a way out of this strange time loop.

name: Bloodline
synopsis: A family is forced to face their past secrets and scars when the black sheep returns home.

name: The Spy
synopsis: Based on the life of Israeli spy Eli Cohen.

name: Shadow and Bone
synopsis: Dark forces conspire against orphan mapmaker Alina Starkov when she unleashes an extraordinary power that could change the fate of her war-torn world.

name: Never Have I Ever
synopsis: The complicated life of a modern-day first generation Indian American teenage girl, inspired by Mindy Kaling's own childhood.

name: How to Sell Drugs Online (Fast)
synopsis: To win back the love of his life, a high school student and his best friend launch Europe's largest online drug business from their teenage bedroom.

name: Soupçons
synopsis: The high-profile murder trial of American novelist Michael Peterson following the death of his wife in 2001.

name: Suburra - La serie
synopsis: In 2008, a fight over land in a seaside town near Rome spirals into a deadly battle between organized crime, corrupt politicians and the Vatican.

name: Inside Bill's Brain: Decoding Bill Gates
synopsis: A documentary that tells Bill Gates' life story as he pursues solutions to some of the world's most complex problems.

name: Maniac
synopsis: Two strangers are drawn to a mysterious pharmaceutical trial for a drug that they're assured will, with no complications or side-effects whatsoever, permanently solve all of their problems. Things do not go as planned.

name: Santa Clarita Diet
synopsis: Sheila and Joel are married real estate agents who live and work in Santa Clarita, California. When Sheila dies, their lives take a dark turn.

name: A Series of Unfortunate Events
synopsis: After the loss of their parents in a mysterious fire, the three Baudelaire children face trials and tribulations attempting to uncover dark family secrets.

name: Conversations with a Killer: The Ted Bundy Tapes
synopsis: A look inside the mind of serial killer Ted Bundy, featuring interviews with him on death row.

name: El Chapo
synopsis: A look at the life of notorious drug kingpin, El Chapo, from his early days in the 1980s working for the Guadalajara Cartel, to his rise to power during the '90s as the head of the Sinaloa Cartel and his ultimate downfall in 2016.

name: Undercover
synopsis: Inspired by real events, undercover agents infiltrate a drug kingpin's operation by posing as a couple at the campground where he spends his weekends.

name: I Think You Should Leave with Tim Robinson
synopsis: In this new sketch show, Tim Robinson and guests spend each segment driving someone to the point of needing -- or desperately wanting -- to leave.

name: You
synopsis: A dangerously charming, intensely obsessive young man goes to extreme measures to insert himself into the lives of those he is transfixed by.

name: Love
synopsis: A program that follows a couple who must navigate the exhilarations and humiliations of intimacy, commitment, and other things they were hoping to avoid.

name: Alias Grace
synopsis: In 19th-century Canada, a psychiatrist weighs whether a murderess should be pardoned due to insanity.

name: The Serpent
synopsis: The twisting, real-life story of Charles Sobhraj, a murderer, thief and seductive master of disguise, who was a hidden darkness in the mid-70's on Asia's hippie trail.
